Lastline PAPI client
-----------------------

This package provides a python implementation of a
client for the Lastline PAPI.

This package is made available to Lastline users 
under a permissive license to make it easier for 
them to make use of or integrate with the Lastline PAPI. 


Possible uses
-----------------------

 - explore PAPI functionality interactively in an ipython shell
 - view or adapt example scripts that use the PAPI client
 - include the papi_client module in python code implementing a 
   custom integration with the Lastline PAPI
 - use this as an example for implementing a PAPI client/integration
   in a different programming langautge

Included in this distribution are:

papi_client.ini.template: Template configuration file
papi_client/: General PAPI client functionality
papi_client/api/: modules implementing individual views of the PAPI
papi_client_test/: unit tests
scripts/papi_shell.py: interactive PAPI client shell
examples: sample scripts making use of the PAPI client


Requirements
-----------------------

The Lastline PAPI client requires:

- python 2.6 or 2.7.
- The python requests module (version 2 or above).
- To use the interactive shell scripts/papi_shell.py, 
  the ipython module is also required.

